                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/geog-306" class="program-course-title">
              GEOG 306 Raster Geo-Information Science (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26578" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Geography (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Geography              : Formal introduction to a computer-based Geographical Information System (GIS). Topics will focus on map analysis and on transforming and displaying spatial data. GIS will be used by students to solve problems in both physical and human geography.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

