                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/geog-316" class="program-course-title">
              GEOG 316 Political Geography (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26592" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Geography (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Geography              : The study of the spatial dimensions of political activities and developments at the regional, national and global levels in historical and contemporary perspective. Presentation of case studies relating to the theoretical framework of political geography.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Benjamin Forest (Fall)                  </p>

    
